                            <comment id="52337" author="keith" created="Wed, 13 Feb 2013 20:44:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Have these patches ever been submitted upstream? &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What are the performance benefits?  EL5 and EL6 are different code bases.  They might not need to the same tweets.  In general the few Kernel proper patches Lustre carries the better. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="50116" author="michael_mckay@xyratex.com" created="Tue, 8 Jan 2013 08:25:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have just uploaded a new set of changes to the review. This contains changes so resolve the 32 bit compilation errors. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="49990" author="keith" created="Fri, 4 Jan 2013 21:41:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Any update? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="48362" author="nrutman" created="Mon, 26 Nov 2012 13:09:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Xyratex-bug-id: &lt;a href=&quot;http://jira-nss.xy01.xyratex.com:8080/browse/MRP-678&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;MRP-678&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="46188" author="keith" created="Mon, 8 Oct 2012 13:32:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Did they become apart of RHEL5?  Have these patches ever been submitted upstream? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45981" author="michael_mckay@xyratex.com" created="Thu, 4 Oct 2012 09:52:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;These are simply a port of the changes that had already been present in rhel5 for some time. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45939" author="keith" created="Wed, 3 Oct 2012 13:58:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you provide some performance numbers about the pro/cons of these changes? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="44860" author="michael_mckay@xyratex.com" created="Fri, 14 Sep 2012 09:01:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have re-based the changes to the latest kernel and they are being reviewed in house by Xyratex first. I will post the changes to the review once they have been approved here.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
